TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Note on Accelerated Dollar Averaging
AU  - Wilson, George W.
Y1  - 1961/01/01
PY  - 1961
DA  - 1961/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.7.2.184
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.7.2.184
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 184
EP  - 186
VL  - 7
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The policy of accelerated dollar averaging as discussed by William T. Morris is an excellent contribution (Morris, W. T. 1959. Some analysis of purchasing policy. Management Sci. 5 (4, July).) is essentially correct. The analysis, however, merits extension beyond the rather abbreviated treatment given in the article cited. Dollar averaging is a type of procurement policy whereby a given amount of money is spent at each purchasing opportunity. The amount actually bought at each period is then a function of the price prevailing at that time.
